159
00:12:19,781 --> 00:12:22,117
Jack.

160
00:12:23,744 --> 00:12:25,746
Hello.

161
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,875
When?

162
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,753
I thought I had
the flu.

163
00:12:32,836 --> 00:12:35,631
I'd still think
I had the flu

164
00:12:35,714 --> 00:12:37,966
if they weren't
telling me otherwise.

165
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:40,844
Well, what are they
telling you?

166
00:12:40,928 --> 00:12:46,433
Pancreatic cancer
of an aggressive nature,

167
00:12:46,517 --> 00:12:48,560
if I heard them right.

168
00:12:48,644 --> 00:12:50,020
Jesus.

169
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:52,564
Well, uh,
what does that mean?

170
00:12:52,648 --> 00:12:55,859
I guess it means
I'm in big trouble.

171
00:12:55,943 --> 00:12:59,238
No, I mean,
can they operate?

172
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:02,741
Maybe. That's what
they said--maybe--

173
00:13:02,824 --> 00:13:05,661
but it sounds
suspiciously like no to me.

174
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:07,746
There's one of them now.

175
00:13:10,707 --> 00:13:14,461
Hey!
I'm not dead yet.

176
00:13:14,545 --> 00:13:16,880
But I am in
the hospital,

177
00:13:16,964 --> 00:13:18,799
which means
that I'm not

178
