I enunciate
that clearly

555
00:30:18,068 --> 00:30:20,445
because I don't want
any mistake.

556
00:30:21,780 --> 00:30:23,699
No troops.

557
00:30:23,740 --> 00:30:27,369
You could say I have
your word on that?

558
00:30:27,452 --> 00:30:29,913
You could, indeed,
because you do.

559
00:30:37,921 --> 00:30:39,840
I'm going
down to 3.

560
00:30:39,882 --> 00:30:41,341
Roger.

561
00:30:44,094 --> 00:30:46,263
Listen up!

562
00:30:46,388 --> 00:30:48,223
Dog tags!

563
00:30:48,307 --> 00:30:51,351
Take 'em off,
pass 'em forward.

564
00:30:51,435 --> 00:30:53,478
Check your pockets
for anything

565
00:30:53,562 --> 00:30:56,857
that can be used
for identification.

566
00:31:04,198 --> 00:31:05,741
We're feet dry.

567
00:31:18,712 --> 00:31:21,632
LZ in sight.
Get ready.

568
00:31:21,715 --> 00:31:23,342
Good luck, boys.

569
00:31:23,425 --> 00:31:25,302
Go get 'em.

570
00:31:28,889 --> 00:31:31,099
Let's take her
down now.

571
00:31:46,782 --> 00:31:48,450
Go! Go! Go!

572
00:33:12,534 --> 00:33:14,661
Hey, Bob.

573
00:33:16,747 --> 00:33:18,165
How you doing?

574
00:33:18,248 --> 00:33:20,584
Good, sir.

575
00:33:20,709 --> 00:33:22,753
Good to see you.

576
00:33:28,175 --> 00:33:30,093
Good morning, Jack.

577
00:33:33,138 --> 00:33:34,556
Yes, yes.

578
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:35,891
Coffee, bagel?

579
00:33:36,016 --> 00:33:37,392
Coffee.
Black, please.

580
00:33:37,476 --> 00:33:38,727
How is
the family?

581
00:33:38,852 --> 00:33:40,521
Um, good, sir.

582
00:33:40,646 --> 00:33:43,690
When do I meet
the other Dr. Ryan?

583
00:33:43,815 --> 00:33:45,567
She's dying to
meet you, sir.

584
00:33:45,692 --> 00:33:47,736
Good. Good.
Sit down.

585
00:33:47,861 --> 00:33:49,279
Thank you.

586
00:33:49,279 --> 00:33:51,114
Thank you.

587
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,033
So...

588
00:33:53,158 --> 00:33:56,411
The cash is
still there, hmm?

589
00:33:56,495 --> 00:33:57,788
Sir?

590
00:33:57,913 --> 00:33:59,873
In Hardin's
offshore accounts.

591
00:33:59,957 --> 00:34:01,416
$650 million.

592
00:34:01,542 --> 00:34:03,210
And change.

593
00:34:03,293 --> 00:34:06,255
And change. And we have
the account numbers.

594
00:34:06,380 --> 00:34:07,714
Yes, sir.

595
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:10,259
Well, what are
we waiting for?

596
00:34:10,384 --> 00:34:11,802
Let's get it.

597
00:34:11,885 --> 00:34:13,387
Let's get it?

598
00:34:13,512 --> 00:34:15,389
Let's turn
this thing around.

599
00:34:15,472 --> 00:34:17,140
$650 million
and change.

600
00:34:17,266 --> 00:34:19,226
It's worth
10 times that

601
00:34:19,351 --> 00:34:20,769
in political
capital.

602
00:34:22,187 --> 00:34:24,064
What?

603
00:34:25,607 --> 00:34:27,693
Uh, well, um...

604
00:34:27,818 --> 00:34:31,321
this connection
between Hardin

605
00:34:31,405 --> 00:34:33,282
and the cartels
is a theory.

606
00:34:33,365 --> 00:34:34,241
Theory?

607
00:34:34,324 --> 00:34:35,659
A theory of mine.

608
00:34:35,742 --> 00:34:36,660
Theory?

609
00:34:36,785 --> 00:34:39,621
Well, I know
the money is there.

610
00:34:39,705 --> 00:34:41,957
Who exactly Hardin
was working for,

611
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:44,084
I don't know
that exactly,

612
00:34:44,209 --> 00:34:47,171
and we would have to
establish that

613
00:34:47,296 --> 00:34:49,673
before we could
seize the money.

614
00:34:51,383 --> 00:34:55,512
So go down there
and establish it.

615
00:34:55,596 --> 00:34:56,972
Go where?

616
00:34:57,055 --> 00:34:58,307
Colombia.

617
00:34:59,683 --> 00:35:02,352
Who, me?

618
00:35:04,479 --> 00:35:07,316
I leave you alone
for two weeks,

619
00:35:07,399 --> 00:35:10,194
and you walk into
a big bear trap.

620
00:35:10,277 --> 00:35:13,071
I don't know what
I was thinking.

621
00:35:13,155 --> 00:35:14,531
You were thinking

622
00:35:14,573 --> 00:35:16,200
about impressing
the President,

623
00:35:16,325 --> 00:35:18,160
and you shouldn't
do that.

624
00:35:18,243 --> 00:35:19,703
November.

625
00:35:20,787 --> 00:35:22,164
January.

626
00:35:22,247 --> 00:35:23,957
Of last year.

627
00:35:26,001 --> 00:35:27,961
There's a guy down there,

628
00:35:28,045 --> 00:35:29,922
Ieast there used to be--

629
00:35:30,047 --> 00:35:31,381
Clark.

630
00:35:31,465 --> 00:35:32,966
We go way back.

631
00:35:33,091 --> 00:35:34,551
Good man.

632
00:35:34,676 --> 00:35:37,596
You hit a brick wall,
look him up.

633
00:35:37,679 --> 00:35:39,431
Admiral Greer.

634
00:35:40,974 --> 00:35:42,351
Chemotherapy.

635
00:35:42,434 --> 00:35:43,977
Ah, shit.

636
00:35:44,102 --> 00:35:46,480
Here we go again.

637
00:35:48,273 --> 00:35:50,108
How is Ritter
behaving?

638
00:35:50,192 --> 00:35:52,486
Ritter? Oh,
Ritter is Ritter.

639
00:35:52,569 --> 00:35:54,404
He's leaving
me alone.

640
00:35:54,488 --> 00:35:55,906
Are you sure?

641
00:35:55,948 --> 00:35:57,783
Watch him like a hawk.

642
00:35:57,866 --> 00:36:00,661
 How you
feeling today, Admiral?

643
00:36:00,744 --> 00:36:02,120
Okey-dokey.

644
00:36:02,246 --> 00:36:04,998
It's just going
to take a few minutes,

645
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:07,793
and we'll get you
back to your room

646
00:36:07,876 --> 00:36:09,169
and all comfortable.

647
00:36:09,294 --> 00:36:12,047
Still a little bit
of nausea from yesterday?

648
00:37:01,638 --> 00:37:03,849
Variable,
this is Knife.

649
00:37:03,932 --> 00:37:06,018
Stand by to copy.
Over.

650
00:37:08,478 --> 00:37:11,064
This is Knife.
Stand by to copy. Over.

651
00:37:11,190 --> 00:37:12,691
Knife,
this is Variable.

652
00:37:12,816 --> 00:37:15,527
Your signal is
five by five. Over.

653
00:37:18,572 --> 00:37:19,740
Clear.

654
00:37:42,429 --> 00:37:45,432
The chicken is
in the pot. Over.

655
00:37:47,267 --> 00:37:48,143
Cook it.

656
00:37:48,185 --> 00:37:49,978
Roger that.

657
00:38:05,702 --> 00:38:07,412
Honey!

658
00:38:07,538 --> 00:38:09,164
I'm late.

659
00:38:09,248 --> 00:38:10,624
Bye.

660
00:38:10,749 --> 00:38:11,875
Have
a good trip.

661
00:38:13,919 --> 00:38:16,588
I'm not going to
say it.

662
00:38:16,672 --> 00:38:18,090
Don't.

663
00:38:18,215 --> 00:38:20,259
Be careful.

664
00:38:47,661 --> 00:38:49,580
And local time is, uh...

665
00:38:49,705 --> 00:38:52,457
well, actually,
it's the same as Washington.

666
00:38:52,541 --> 00:38:53,959
It's 11:16 a.m.

667
00:38:54,084 --> 00:38:57,504
There'll be a temperature
of about 69 degrees Fahrenheit.

668
00:39:03,468 --> 00:39:04,803
Dr. Ryan!

669
00:39:06,054 --> 00:39:07,598
Dr. Ryan!

670
00:39:14,605 --> 00:39:16,982
DEA Special Agent
Jean Fowler.

671
00:39:17,107 --> 00:39:18,233
Hi, Jean.

672
00:39:18,317 --> 00:39:20,319
First time in Bogota, right?

673
00:39:20,444 --> 00:39:21,486
Let's not stand here

674
00:39:21,612 --> 00:39:23,071
and let somebody
take a shot at you.

675
00:39:23,155 --> 00:39:25,115
Hell, you just
got here.

676
00:39:25,199 --> 00:39:27,576
Come on, sir.
Let's go.

677
00:39:40,339 --> 00:39:41,882
These two are--

678
00:39:41,965 --> 00:39:43,175
They're brothers.

679
00:39:43,217 --> 00:39:44,468
Brothers.

680
00:39:46,553 --> 00:39:47,971
Don't do that.

681
00:39:48,013 --> 00:39:49,389
Give Dr. Ryan

682
00:39:49,515 --> 00:39:51,391
more air back here,
please.

683
00:39:51,475 --> 00:39:52,476
Bulletproof.

684
00:40:00,192 --> 00:40:02,194
We don't have
a picture.

685
00:40:02,277 --> 00:40:04,071
Escobedo's
lntelligence Officer.

686
00:40:07,157 --> 00:40:10,702
Invisible man, huh?

687
00:40:11,119 --> 00:40:13,830
Gently, gently
with your hands.

688
00:40:13,914 --> 00:40:16,959
 Luis, put
your hands together!

689
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:19,044
No! Your hands!

690
00:40:19,127 --> 00:40:20,504
Together!

691
00:40:20,587 --> 00:40:22,464
Good. Good.

692
00:40:22,548 --> 00:40:24,383
Luis,
watch the canter!

693
00:40:24,466 --> 00:40:26,343
Now trot.

694
00:40:26,385 --> 00:40:27,719
Yes!

695
00:40:27,803 --> 00:40:29,221
Very good!

696
00:40:29,263 --> 00:40:31,098
Ha ha ha ha!

697
00:40:31,181 --> 00:40:33,517
Press
with your legs.

698
00:40:33,559 --> 00:40:35,060
Yes.

699
00:40:37,396 --> 00:40:39,273
We lost
another plane.

700
00:40:39,356 --> 00:40:41,817
Now go to
a shorter trot.

701
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:43,402
O.K.

702
00:40:46,071 --> 00:40:47,948
Who is doing this?

703
00:40:48,031 --> 00:40:50,409
If I had to guess?

704
00:40:50,492 --> 00:40:52,870
That's not
what I asked you.

705
00:40:52,953 --> 00:40:54,413
I can guess.

706
00:40:54,496 --> 00:40:57,291
Someone has been talking
to the drug police.

707
00:40:57,374 --> 00:40:58,792
Now, that's impossible.

708
00:40:58,876 --> 00:41:01,128
If anyone spoke
to the police,

709
00:41:01,211 --> 00:41:02,129
I would know.

710
00:41:02,212 --> 00:41:03,755
Ernesto.

711
00:41:05,215 --> 00:41:07,593
You think
one of the others

712
00:41:09,595 --> 00:41:12,264
after what I did
to the American?

713
00:41:12,347 --> 00:41:14,725
That wasn't quite
the deterrent

714
00:41:14,808 --> 00:41:16,602
you thought
it would be.

715
00:41:16,643 --> 00:41:18,687
Find out who it is.

716
00:41:25,527 --> 00:41:28,447
What do you make
of this, Colonel?

717
00:41:30,115 --> 00:41:31,658
An opportunity.

718
00:41:33,535 --> 00:41:35,829
An opportunity, Sipo.

719
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,178
Good afternoon.

720
00:41:51,220 --> 00:41:53,263
Afternoon.
Messages, please.

721
00:41:54,598 --> 00:41:56,016
Dr. Ryan.

722
00:41:56,058 --> 00:41:57,476
Clark.

723
00:41:57,476 --> 00:41:58,852
I'm sorry I'm late.

724
00:41:58,894 --> 00:42:00,771
I got
10 minutes.

725
00:42:00,812 --> 00:42:03,065
O.K.

726
00:42:04,316 --> 00:42:06,109
I'm positive
that Hardin

727
00:42:06,193 --> 00:42:08,028
was tied
into the cartels.

728
00:42:08,028 --> 00:42:09,404
It's definitely
drug money.

729
00:42:09,446 --> 00:42:11,323
But you can't
prove it.

730
00:42:11,365 --> 00:42:12,824
So far.

731
00:42:12,824 --> 00:42:15,702
Mind if I ask you
a question?

732
00:42:15,702 --> 00:42:16,995
No.

733
00:42:17,037 --> 00:42:19,706
Why are you
telling me all this?

734
00:42:19,790 --> 00:42:23,585
I've been out of the game
for a long time.

735
00:42:23,669 --> 00:42:25,462
Oh. Well, I was told

736
00:42:25,546 --> 00:42:27,798
you were
wired in down here,

737
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:29,716
that you knew
the town,

738
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,720
Who told you that?

739
00:42:33,762 --> 00:42:36,515
Jim Greer.

740
00:42:38,725 --> 00:42:40,602
How's he doing?

741
00:42:42,938 --> 00:42:44,940
Well, he's not good.

742
00:42:46,942 --> 00:42:48,402
It's cancer...

743
00:42:48,485 --> 00:42:50,070
terminal.

744
00:42:53,073 --> 00:42:54,533
He's a good man.

745
00:42:54,616 --> 00:42:56,285
The best.

746
00:43:03,208 --> 00:43:05,752
You a coffee drinker,
Dr. Ryan?

747
00:43:08,046 --> 00:43:09,673
Yeah, I like coffee.

748
00:43:09,756 --> 00:43:11,592
Try the Lindo brand.

749
00:43:11,675 --> 00:43:12,801
Lindo.

750
00:43:12,885 --> 00:43:14,887
I think
you'll like it.

751
00:43:20,517 --> 00:43:21,852
Mr. President,

752
00:43:21,935 --> 00:43:24,062
I've got some good news.

753
00:43:24,146 --> 00:43:25,272
Good.

754
00:43:25,355 --> 00:43:26,732
Hardin's partner
down here

755
00:43:26,773 --> 00:43:29,610
was someone you may
have heard of--

756
00:43:29,651 --> 00:43:30,903
Ernesto Escobedo.

757
00:43:30,944 --> 00:43:32,321
That figures.

758
00:43:32,404 --> 00:43:33,780
Now, is this
another

759
00:43:33,822 --> 00:43:35,282
of your
theories, Ryan?

760
00:43:35,324 --> 00:43:38,577
No. I think we can
call this one fact.

761
00:43:38,660 --> 00:43:41,455
Escobedo, like every other
drug lord down here,

762
00:43:41,538 --> 00:43:43,373
was also running
legitimate businesses,

763
00:43:43,457 --> 00:43:45,292
and Hardin
was doing business

764
00:43:45,375 --> 00:43:46,877
with these businesses,

765
00:43:46,919 --> 00:43:47,794
importing,

766
00:43:47,878 --> 00:43:49,129
among other things,
coffee,

767
00:43:49,213 --> 00:43:52,007
which in and of itself
means nothing,

768
00:43:52,090 --> 00:43:54,218
but he was
paying too much

769
00:43:54,301 --> 00:43:55,385
for this coffee--

770
00:43:55,427 --> 00:43:56,803
$6,200 a pound,

771
00:43:56,845 --> 00:43:58,430
if my arithmetic
is correct.

772
00:43:58,514 --> 00:44:00,015
Well, that's
expensive coffee.

773
00:44:00,098 --> 00:44:01,600
Yes, sir.
I'd agree.

774
00:44:01,683 --> 00:44:03,060
This is good news.

775
00:44:05,062 --> 00:44:06,063
Um, sir...

776
00:44:06,146 --> 00:44:08,899
I have other news
which isn't so good.

777
00:44:08,982 --> 00:44:11,276
Oh, God.

778
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:14,863
Um...DEA here feels
that the Colombian government

779
00:44:14,947 --> 00:44:17,199
would want
the seized funds...

780
00:44:20,202 --> 00:44:21,912
This is our money.

781
00:44:21,954 --> 00:44:23,330
We found it.

782
00:44:23,372 --> 00:44:25,832
We could try
telling them that.

783
00:44:25,916 --> 00:44:27,292
Try? Tell them!

784
00:44:27,376 --> 00:44:29,294
Or don't.
I don't care.

785
00:44:29,378 --> 00:44:30,879
With all due respect--

786
00:44:30,879 --> 00:44:33,215
Tell them
this is our money.

787
00:44:33,298 --> 00:44:35,676
I wouldn't know
what to say.

788
00:44:35,717 --> 00:44:37,719
I'm not a negotiator.

789
00:44:37,761 --> 00:44:40,597
Don't you know someone
in their government?

790
00:44:40,639 --> 00:44:43,809
I went to school with
their Attorney General.

791
00:44:43,851 --> 00:44:45,435
Jacobs will come down.

792
00:44:45,477 --> 00:44:47,229
He'll take care of it.

793
00:44:47,312 --> 00:44:48,772
This is our money.

794
00:44:49,815 --> 00:44:51,024
Thank--

795
00:44:52,484 --> 00:44:54,027
Thank you.

796
00:44:56,822 --> 00:44:58,824
I hate this job.

797
00:46:09,144 --> 00:46:10,646
Uh!

798
00:46:13,148 --> 00:46:14,900
Eyes up!

799
00:46:18,111 --> 00:46:20,447
Demo team, up!

800
00:46:25,661 --> 00:46:27,079
Device set!

801
00:46:27,162 --> 00:46:29,456
Fire in the hole!

802
00:46:33,669 --> 00:46:35,546
Let's go!
Move out!

803
00:46:39,216 --> 00:46:40,676
Down! Down!

804
00:46:57,276 --> 00:46:59,361
Whoever did this
is dead.

805
00:47:01,113 --> 00:47:04,491
Whoever did this
to me is dead!

806
00:47:05,868 --> 00:47:07,703
Do you hear me?

807
00:47:07,786 --> 00:47:10,497
Are you
listening to me?

808
00:47:22,759 --> 00:47:25,470
We'll go over it
on the plane again.

809
00:47:25,554 --> 00:47:28,015
Mr. Jacobs,
could you sign these?

810
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:30,976
Moira...

811
00:47:31,059 --> 00:47:32,603
why don't you

812
00:47:32,644 --> 00:47:34,104
call in sick
tomorrow?

813
00:47:34,188 --> 00:47:35,522
And the next day.

814
00:47:35,606 --> 00:47:37,608
I won't
tell anybody.

815
00:47:37,691 --> 00:47:39,568
Just because
you're not here

816
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:41,945
doesn't mean
there's nothing to do.

817
00:47:42,029 --> 00:47:43,238
Your itinerary.

818
00:47:45,282 --> 00:47:47,701
You work too hard.

819
00:47:47,784 --> 00:47:49,161
Adios.

820
00:47:59,004 --> 00:48:00,422
Director Jacobs'
office.

821
00:48:00,506 --> 00:48:03,550
Oh, yes. Hello.

822
00:48:03,634 --> 00:48:04,968
All right.

823
00:48:05,052 --> 00:48:06,428
Uh...l do have

824
00:48:06,470 --> 00:48:07,846
a tentative
schedule.

825
00:48:26,740 --> 00:48:28,116
Landa y Landa.

826
00:48:28,200 --> 00:48:29,535
Roberto Landa, please.

827
00:48:29,618 --> 00:48:31,245
This is Moira Wolfson.

828
00:48:31,328 --> 00:48:33,205
One moment, please,
Ms. Wolfson.

829
00:48:33,288 --> 00:48:35,958
I'll see
if I can find him.

830
00:48:35,999 --> 00:48:38,085
He's on
the factory floor.

831
00:48:42,756 --> 00:48:44,049
Yes.

832
00:48:44,091 --> 00:48:46,301
A Moira Wolfson
is calling.

833
00:48:46,385 --> 00:48:49,680
I told her you were
on the factory floor.

