01:09:33,771 --> 01:09:35,139
Enrique!

100
01:09:36,345 --> 01:09:38,558
Good
to see you!

101
01:09:38,599 --> 01:09:39,886
It was not easy.

102
01:09:39,966 --> 01:09:41,133
Enrique,
how are you?

103
01:09:41,213 --> 01:09:43,346
Rojas...

104
01:09:43,426 --> 01:09:45,557
Diaz.

105
01:09:47,006 --> 01:09:50,143
Oh, what the hell
is this?

106
01:09:50,184 --> 01:09:52,315
What the hell
is this?

107
01:09:53,201 --> 01:09:54,609
Ha ha ha!

108
01:09:54,689 --> 01:09:56,056
My new toy.

109
01:09:56,137 --> 01:09:57,787
You like it?

110
01:09:57,867 --> 01:10:00,281
You see this?

111
01:10:00,361 --> 01:10:01,528
That's
your new target,

112
01:10:09,815 --> 01:10:11,705
Variable,
this is Easy Rhino.

113
01:10:11,785 --> 01:10:13,234
Do you copy? Over.

114
01:10:13,314 --> 01:10:15,205
Loud and clear,
Easy Rhino.

115
01:10:15,245 --> 01:10:18,222
Do we have a gig?
Over.

116
01:10:18,302 --> 01:10:19,871
That's a rog.

117
01:10:25,462 --> 01:10:27,353
Target is lit.

118
01:10:28,962 --> 01:10:30,652
Start the music.

119
01:10:30,692 --> 01:10:33,548
Into attack.

120
01:10:34,594 --> 01:10:36,002
Pickle is hot.

121
01:10:36,082 --> 01:10:38,094
Target is acquired
and lit.

122
01:10:38,174 --> 01:10:39,462
Coming down.

123
01:10:45,696 --> 01:10:47,265
Vega...

124
01:10:47,346 --> 01:10:50,645
Iooks like
a full house.

125
01:10:58,287 --> 01:10:59,615
Damn it!

126
01:10:59,695 --> 01:11:02,028
Why doesn't he
fix this road?

127
01:11:02,109 --> 01:11:04,161
Shit.

128
01:11:04,241 --> 01:11:06,212
I thought
we had everybody.

129
01:11:06,292 --> 01:11:09,470
Keep the target
painted.

130
01:11:36,905 --> 01:11:38,675
Sir.

131
01:11:43,060 --> 01:11:44,749
Boom!

132
01:11:53,680 --> 01:11:55,168
Mother of God.

133
01:11:58,467 --> 01:12:01,765
Circular error
probability zero.

134
01:12:01,845 --> 01:12:03,898
Impact with high-order
detonation.

135
01:12:03,937 --> 01:12:05,667
Have a nice day.

136
01:12:11,540 --> 01:12:14,396
The man is completely
out of control.

137
01:12:16,367 --> 01:12:19,223
The man is completely
out of control.

138
01:12:19,304 --> 01:12:21,436
Completely out of control.

139
01:12:23,125 --> 01:12:25,137
His name is Cortez.

140
01:12:25,177 --> 01:12:27,269
Felix Cortez.

141
01:12:27,350 --> 01:12:30,165
He was a colonel
in Cuba's lntelligence Service

142
01:12:30,246 --> 01:12:31,734
until a few years ago.

143
01:12:34,792 --> 01:12:36,039
in Puerto Rico.

144
01:12:36,078 --> 01:12:38,372
Disappeared again.

145
01:12:40,463 --> 01:12:42,354
to a Cali cartel subject.

146
01:12:42,434 --> 01:12:44,687
I'll fax you
what I have.

147
01:12:47,663 --> 01:12:48,992
I can't do that.

148
01:12:49,072 --> 01:12:51,164
Not you. The police.
The Colombians.

149
01:12:51,244 --> 01:12:52,853
The Colombian police,
Jack,

150
01:12:52,933 --> 01:12:55,750
do not pick up
members of the cartel

151
01:12:55,830 --> 01:12:59,008
unless they've got
a death wish.

152
01:12:59,088 --> 01:13:01,904
Wait a minute.

153
01:13:01,984 --> 01:13:03,312
Oh, Jesus.

154
01:13:03,392 --> 01:13:05,404
Jack, something's
happened here.

155
01:13:18,437 --> 01:13:20,972
At least 30 people
were killed,

156
01:13:21,052 --> 01:13:22,621
including
women and children.

157
01:13:22,701 --> 01:13:24,189
Police report
the bomb exploded

158
01:13:24,230 --> 01:13:27,810
in a car belonging
to one of Rojas' associates.

159
01:13:27,891 --> 01:13:29,379
Jack! Jack!

160
01:13:29,459 --> 01:13:31,953
Yeah.
Did this just happen?

161
01:13:31,994 --> 01:13:33,441
Just now.

162
01:13:33,522 --> 01:13:35,855
...counsel of the Cali
cocaine cartel

163
01:13:35,935 --> 01:13:37,021
and a businessman.

164
01:13:37,102 --> 01:13:39,113
Send me
all the stuff.

165
01:13:39,194 --> 01:13:41,286
We'll put a tail on him
if we spot him.

166
01:13:41,366 --> 01:13:43,016
If he's still alive.

167
01:13:43,056 --> 01:13:44,464
I got to go.

168
01:13:44,504 --> 01:13:46,918
...the latest in a series
of mysterious explosions.

169
01:13:47,038 --> 01:13:48,929
The cops
claim the violence...

170
01:13:49,010 --> 01:13:50,659
You said it would be
a surgical strike.

171
01:13:50,739 --> 01:13:52,268
It was.
It was perfect.

172
01:13:54,319 --> 01:13:56,452
"Hurt them."
That's what you said.

173
01:13:56,532 --> 01:13:58,302
I know what I said, Bobby.

174
01:13:58,342 --> 01:14:00,112
Are you changing
your mind?

175
01:14:00,192 --> 01:14:02,727
No, I'm not.

176
01:14:02,808 --> 01:14:04,376
I hadn't counted on

177
01:14:04,457 --> 01:14:06,829
this kind of
collateral damage,

178
01:14:06,870 --> 01:14:08,721
and neither did he.

179
01:14:08,801 --> 01:14:11,577
It'll be interpreted
like I said it would--

180
01:14:11,657 --> 01:14:12,583
rivalry ended

181
01:14:12,663 --> 01:14:14,955
in the blast
of a car-bomb.

182
01:14:15,036 --> 01:14:16,363
Good night.

183
01:14:16,363 --> 01:14:18,415
...indicates that
the guerrilla offensive

184
01:14:18,455 --> 01:14:19,863
against the cartels

185
01:14:19,943 --> 01:14:23,041
by antidrug units
of the Colombian...

186
01:14:31,971 --> 01:14:33,057
You finish the report?

187
01:14:33,138 --> 01:14:34,304
Hot off the press.

188
01:14:34,385 --> 01:14:35,672
Thanks.

189
01:14:37,966 --> 01:14:40,701
Any chances any of these
bombing victims' names

190
01:14:40,781 --> 01:14:41,867
are aliases?

191
01:14:41,948 --> 01:14:44,321
No. All l.D.s
have been confirmed.

192
01:14:44,402 --> 01:14:46,292
Who are you
hoping for?

193
01:14:46,332 --> 01:14:47,741
He's not here.
Cortez.

194
01:14:47,821 --> 01:14:49,510
He's not here.

195
01:14:49,590 --> 01:14:52,246
Um...

196
01:14:52,327 --> 01:14:54,780
why was Operations
copied on this?

197
01:14:54,820 --> 01:14:56,751
Ritter requested it.

198
01:14:56,791 --> 01:14:58,240
Ritter, huh?

199
01:14:58,320 --> 01:15:00,734
You look
very nice today.

200
01:15:00,773 --> 01:15:02,665
Thank you.

201
01:15:16,623 --> 01:15:18,353
Car-bomb.

202
01:15:27,243 --> 01:15:30,099
What happens when
a car-bomb goes off?

203
01:15:30,179 --> 01:15:31,587
It explodes.

204
01:15:31,628 --> 01:15:33,961
Right. It blows up
and out.

205
01:15:34,041 --> 01:15:35,409
And a missile?

206
01:15:35,449 --> 01:15:36,776
Mm-hmm.

207
01:15:39,311 --> 01:15:40,599
This deeper crater?

208
01:15:40,679 --> 01:15:42,006
That's characteristic.

209
01:15:42,087 --> 01:15:44,782
O.K. Bring up
the satellite photo now.

210
01:15:49,851 --> 01:15:52,103
HMX...

211
01:15:52,143 --> 01:15:53,672
and TNT.

212
01:15:53,713 --> 01:15:56,046
When you
mix it 70/30,

213
01:15:56,126 --> 01:15:58,499
you get the compound
called octol.

214
01:15:58,540 --> 01:16:00,873
Put enough explosives
in a car,

215
01:16:00,953 --> 01:16:02,804
you'll get
a big crater.

216
01:16:02,884 --> 01:16:05,337
Would the car
still be there?

217
01:16:05,418 --> 01:16:08,797
There would be pieces
all around here.

218
01:16:08,878 --> 01:16:11,532
And where is
octol made?

219
01:16:11,613 --> 01:16:13,383
Lots of places--

220
01:16:13,463 --> 01:16:16,078
Europe, the U.S.

221
01:16:16,159 --> 01:16:17,767
but nobody uses it.

222
01:16:17,849 --> 01:16:20,664
Nobody can afford it
except the military.

223
01:16:20,745 --> 01:16:22,836
An aerial bomb
would do that,

224
01:16:22,917 --> 01:16:26,134
but that's not
an aerial bomb.

225
01:16:26,215 --> 01:16:27,583
It's not?

226
01:16:27,663 --> 01:16:28,790
No.

227
01:16:28,871 --> 01:16:32,330
There is also a cellulose
residue on everything.

228
01:16:32,370 --> 01:16:34,543
There should
be shrapnel here,

229
01:16:34,623 --> 01:16:36,111
but there isn't.

230
01:16:36,192 --> 01:16:38,364
No bomb fragments.

231
01:17:20,039 --> 01:17:24,342
"Cellulose encased
laser-guided bomb."

232
01:17:26,595 --> 01:17:28,486
Paper.

233
01:17:32,428 --> 01:17:34,118
The Americans are here?

234
01:18:02,398 --> 01:18:03,966
Ohh...

235
01:18:04,006 --> 01:18:06,299
We have something in common.

236
01:18:06,380 --> 01:18:08,753
Neither of us
can implement policy

237
01:18:10,764 --> 01:18:12,132
from our employer.

238
01:18:12,212 --> 01:18:14,546
We have something else
in common.

239
01:18:14,586 --> 01:18:17,925
We both know there are
American troops in Colombia

240
01:18:18,005 --> 01:18:20,780
fighting an illegal war.

241
01:18:20,821 --> 01:18:24,642
I will be staying
at the Hotel Paloma de Oro

242
01:18:24,683 --> 01:18:26,573
in Panama City
on Wednesday.

243
01:18:26,654 --> 01:18:27,861
I suggest we meet.

244
01:19:17,621 --> 01:19:20,074
6, this is Point.
Over.

245
01:19:20,155 --> 01:19:22,207
6 here.

246
01:19:22,247 --> 01:19:26,391
The stuff's here,
and there's a lot of it.

247
01:19:26,430 --> 01:19:30,695
I'm also looking
at 100 to 150 men, armed,

248
01:19:30,775 --> 01:19:32,102
waiting around
for something.

249
01:19:32,183 --> 01:19:33,269
Over.

250
01:19:33,349 --> 01:19:35,200
Colombian Army?
Over.

251
01:19:39,625 --> 01:19:41,999
Negative. They look
like mercenaries.

252
01:19:42,038 --> 01:19:43,285
Over.

253
01:19:43,326 --> 01:19:44,694
All right.

254
01:19:44,774 --> 01:19:47,147
Get on back here.
Abort mission.

255
01:19:47,188 --> 01:19:48,716
Abort mission.
Out.

256
01:19:50,566 --> 01:19:53,221
150 armed men, huh?

257
01:20:13,255 --> 01:20:15,588
Raise your arms,
please.

258
01:20:30,149 --> 01:20:33,006
Thank you for responding
to my note.

259
01:20:33,046 --> 01:20:36,466
You should know
that I had nothing to do

260
01:20:36,546 --> 01:20:38,154
with Mr. Jacobs' death.

261
01:20:38,235 --> 01:20:40,769
It was an act
of madness,

262
01:20:40,850 --> 01:20:44,752
but a typical one
from the men I work for.

263
01:20:44,832 --> 01:20:46,361
What do you want?

264
01:20:46,441 --> 01:20:49,137
Same as you.
Mineral water.

265
01:20:49,217 --> 01:20:52,999
Can we agree that as long
as Americans demand drugs,

266
01:20:53,079 --> 01:20:54,607
someone
will supply them?

267
01:20:54,688 --> 01:20:57,866
Look. I don't want
to be here long.

268
01:20:57,946 --> 01:21:00,079
You mentioned
a gang war.

269
01:21:00,159 --> 01:21:01,808
What does that mean?

270
01:21:01,888 --> 01:21:04,704
That you and I
want the same thing.

271
01:21:04,745 --> 01:21:06,152
The same thing.
Really?

272
01:21:06,193 --> 01:21:08,365
Though you've
done all the work.

273
01:21:08,446 --> 01:21:11,261
You've taken care
of the little fish.

274
01:21:11,342 --> 01:21:15,123
I will take care of
the one that got away.

275
01:21:15,204 --> 01:21:16,651
Once Escobedo
is gone,

276
01:21:19,709 --> 01:21:22,082
your country,
your people...

277
01:21:22,162 --> 01:21:25,140
by restructuring
the drug trade,

278
01:21:25,220 --> 01:21:26,587
by regulating it.

279
01:21:26,668 --> 01:21:29,202
What will you say
if I promise you

280
01:21:29,283 --> 01:21:31,616
I will reduce
the cocaine shipments

281
01:21:31,696 --> 01:21:33,990
to your country
by half?

282
01:21:34,029 --> 01:21:35,639
That you've
been using

283
01:21:35,719 --> 01:21:37,570
too much
of your product.

284
01:21:37,650 --> 01:21:39,018
Ha ha!

285
01:21:39,058 --> 01:21:40,948
I can also
promise you

286
01:21:40,989 --> 01:21:42,879
regular quotas
on major arrests

287
01:21:42,920 --> 01:21:45,776
that your police
can take credit for.

288
01:21:45,816 --> 01:21:47,224
Imagine that--

289
01:21:47,304 --> 01:21:48,793
dramatic seizures,

290
01:21:48,874 --> 01:21:50,080
drastic reductions,

291
01:21:50,160 --> 01:21:52,051
no more
senseless violence.

292
01:21:52,091 --> 01:21:55,109
You'll have
your victory.

293
01:21:58,849 --> 01:22:00,861
In return for what?

294
01:22:00,901 --> 01:22:04,079
Well, I also
need a victory

295
01:22:04,119 --> 01:22:05,568
to establish
my position

296
01:22:05,607 --> 01:22:07,820
with what's left
of the cartel

297
01:22:07,901 --> 01:22:10,434
so I can help you.

298
01:22:10,515 --> 01:22:12,808
I need to defeat
those soldiers

299
01:22:12,889 --> 01:22:14,739
blowing up
everything they see.

300
01:22:14,779 --> 01:22:17,957
Give me maps
of their locations.

301
01:22:18,037 --> 01:22:20,572
Cut off
their communications.

302
01:22:27,732 --> 01:22:31,031
DEA's sending the audio
surveillance tape.

303
01:22:31,112 --> 01:22:33,887
I haven't got it yet.

304
01:22:35,939 --> 01:22:38,312
You know what
you think about--

305
01:22:39,801 --> 01:22:41,489
when you're
lying here?

306
01:22:42,737 --> 01:22:45,070
You know
you're going to die,

307
01:22:45,151 --> 01:22:46,961
and you think...

308
01:22:47,041 --> 01:22:48,892
that's all right.

309
01:22:48,972 --> 01:22:50,823
You lived
a long time.

310
01:22:50,903 --> 01:22:54,564
You got a family
that loved you.

311
01:22:54,644 --> 01:22:59,109
You had a job that
you thought made a difference,

312
01:22:59,149 --> 01:23:01,845
that you thought
was honorable...

313
01:23:01,925 --> 01:23:05,384
and then
you see this.

314
01:23:09,689 --> 01:23:12,504
I'm afraid
if I dig any deeper,

315
01:23:12,545 --> 01:23:16,004
no one's going to
like what I find.

316
01:23:20,349 --> 01:23:24,573
You took an oath...

317
01:23:24,653 --> 01:23:27,267
if you recall...

318
01:23:30,003 --> 01:23:32,779
when you first came
to work for me,

319
01:23:32,819 --> 01:23:36,641
and I don't mean to
the National Security Advisor

320
01:23:36,681 --> 01:23:39,537
of the United States.

321
01:23:39,577 --> 01:23:42,232
I mean to his boss.

322
01:23:43,801 --> 01:23:47,381
And I don't mean
the President.

323
01:23:47,461 --> 01:23:50,478
You gave your word...

324
01:23:50,559 --> 01:23:54,019
to...his boss.

325
01:23:54,099 --> 01:23:56,553
You gave your word

326
01:23:56,634 --> 01:24:02,345
to the people
of the United States.

327
01:24:02,386 --> 01:24:05,564
Your word
is who you are.

328
01:24:10,954 --> 01:24:12,844
What else
you got there?

329
01:24:17,712 --> 01:24:20,488
I brought you
some new magazines.

330
01:24:30,061 --> 01:24:31,953
The situation
in East Timor

331
01:24:32,033 --> 01:24:33,441
seems to have
stabilized

332
01:24:33,480 --> 01:24:34,849
during the day.

333
01:24:34,929 --> 01:24:36,337
Good.

334
01:24:36,377 --> 01:24:37,785
Is that it?

335
01:24:37,866 --> 01:24:39,716
Except for
the other thing.

336
01:24:39,797 --> 01:24:41,607
We've accomplished
a lot.

337
01:24:41,687 --> 01:24:44,342
We're seeing
tangible results.

338
01:24:44,382 --> 01:24:45,830
Drug shipments
are down.

339
01:24:45,871 --> 01:24:48,244
Price on the street
is rising.

340
01:24:48,284 --> 01:24:50,174
Perception is that
the administration

341
01:24:50,215 --> 01:24:51,703
is doing
something right.

342
01:24:51,784 --> 01:24:54,801
What's
the bad news?

343
01:24:56,651 --> 01:24:59,024
I'm concerned about
this latest incident--

344
01:24:59,106 --> 01:25:01,439
the car-bomb
coming so soon

345
01:25:01,478 --> 01:25:03,168
after Jacobs'
assassination.

346
01:25:03,249 --> 01:25:07,070
It's the kind of thing
reporters live for.

347
01:25:07,150 --> 01:25:09,605
They'd love to
make a connection.

348
01:25:09,685 --> 01:25:11,736
And you think
they will.

349
01:25:11,817 --> 01:25:15,236
I think it's time
the whole thing went away.

350
01:25:16,925 --> 01:25:18,816
If that's
what you think.

351
01:25:18,856 --> 01:25:20,747
I think so.

352
01:25:22,437 --> 01:25:24,569
Then it should
go away.

353
01:25:24,609 --> 01:25:26,338
It never happened.

354
01:25:27,827 --> 01:25:29,396
Yes, sir.

355
01:25:31,568 --> 01:25:35,269
Well, I mean,
it's possible.

356
01:25:35,349 --> 01:25:36,476
It would be
a lot easier

357
01:25:36,556 --> 01:25:38,689
if you told me
whose system

358
01:25:38,769 --> 01:25:40,458
you wanted me
to break into.

359
01:25:40,538 --> 01:25:41,464
Good morning,
Dr. Ryan.

360
01:25:41,585 --> 01:25:42,590
Morning.

361
01:26:01,014 --> 01:26:02,422
Well...

362
01:26:02,462 --> 01:26:05,198
we're way beyond
birthdays now.

363
01:26:05,278 --> 01:26:07,893
I'm going to
have to write

364
01:26:07,973 --> 01:26:10,105
a special program here.

365
01:26:13,444 --> 01:26:14,812
Right.

366
01:26:21,127 --> 01:26:22,615
O.K., sweetheart...

367
01:26:22,656 --> 01:26:25,391
Iet's get to work.

368
01:26:25,432 --> 01:26:27,644
Fine. Good.

369
01:26:28,730 --> 01:26:30,018
Yes!

370
01:26:31,586 --> 01:26:33,235
Here we go.

371
01:27:07,871 --> 01:27:09,359
Jesus.

372
01:27:28,145 --> 01:27:31,404
"Reciprocity."
What's that?

373
01:27:43,069 --> 01:27:44,798
I forgot
to tell you.

