01:50:19,110 --> 01:50:21,161
Arms up.

652
01:50:21,283 --> 01:50:23,535
Arms up!

653
01:50:37,132 --> 01:50:38,902
He's in.

654
01:50:42,643 --> 01:50:45,499
Bird, this is Variable.
Over.

655
01:50:47,470 --> 01:50:50,326
Bird, this is Variable.
Over.

656
01:51:06,256 --> 01:51:08,347
Dr. Ryan.

657
01:51:23,110 --> 01:51:24,518
Sit down.

658
01:51:24,599 --> 01:51:27,496
What can I
do for you?

659
01:51:27,576 --> 01:51:31,679
Well, I didn't know
who else to turn to.

660
01:51:31,760 --> 01:51:34,977
I have a problem.

661
01:51:35,058 --> 01:51:36,626
An associate
of mine,

662
01:51:36,667 --> 01:51:39,000
a coffee buyer
and his assistant,

663
01:51:39,081 --> 01:51:40,851
were on
a business trip

664
01:51:40,931 --> 01:51:42,259
in this area.

665
01:51:42,339 --> 01:51:43,948
They unexpectedly
disappeared yesterday.

666
01:51:44,029 --> 01:51:45,396
I'm very concerned.

667
01:51:45,476 --> 01:51:46,844
Coffee buyer.

668
01:51:46,925 --> 01:51:49,258
Mmm. It's very
important to me

669
01:51:49,338 --> 01:51:50,706
to find them.

670
01:51:50,787 --> 01:51:52,516
Coffee buying
is becoming

671
01:51:52,597 --> 01:51:54,206
a very dangerous
business.

672
01:51:54,246 --> 01:51:56,096
Yes.

673
01:51:56,137 --> 01:52:00,441
Yes. Well, it was
for Peter Hardin.

674
01:52:02,412 --> 01:52:03,499
Who?

675
01:52:03,579 --> 01:52:05,429
A client
of Lindo Coffee.

676
01:52:05,469 --> 01:52:07,360
Lindo Coffee
has many clients.

677
01:52:07,400 --> 01:52:10,618
Well, you must have
heard of this one.

678
01:52:10,698 --> 01:52:12,308
He owed your company

679
01:52:12,388 --> 01:52:14,239
a great deal
of money.

680
01:52:14,319 --> 01:52:17,015
Oh? Well,
I'll have to talk

681
01:52:17,095 --> 01:52:19,468
to Accounting
about that.

682
01:52:19,509 --> 01:52:22,646
$650 million.

683
01:52:24,738 --> 01:52:26,951
And change.

684
01:52:29,042 --> 01:52:31,335
Are you offering
to help me

685
01:52:31,415 --> 01:52:34,271
with the collection
of an unpaid debt?

686
01:52:34,312 --> 01:52:35,398
No.

687
01:52:35,479 --> 01:52:37,248
What are you offering?

688
01:52:40,265 --> 01:52:42,639
Felix Cortez
has sold you out.

689
01:52:42,679 --> 01:52:45,535
His next move
is to murder you

690
01:52:45,576 --> 01:52:47,466
and take over
the cartel.

691
01:52:47,507 --> 01:52:49,558
Where is
my tape recorder?

692
01:52:55,270 --> 01:52:57,684
Play the tape.

693
01:53:11,723 --> 01:53:13,774
Mira! Mira! Mira!

694
01:53:29,100 --> 01:53:31,192
Let's move.

695
01:53:59,874 --> 01:54:03,213
I'd like you to meet
my new friend--

696
01:54:03,293 --> 01:54:04,661
Dr. Ryan.

697
01:54:04,742 --> 01:54:06,753
Doctor? Why?
ls somebody sick?

698
01:54:19,987 --> 01:54:21,877
What does he want?

699
01:54:23,849 --> 01:54:26,906
The safe return
of his associates.

700
01:54:26,986 --> 01:54:31,050
And, uh, what does
he offer us in return?

701
01:54:31,090 --> 01:54:32,497
You.

702
01:54:38,492 --> 01:54:41,066
Whatever this man
told you is a lie.

703
01:54:41,147 --> 01:54:42,997
He lies for a living.

704
01:54:43,078 --> 01:54:44,968
He's in the lntelligence
business.

705
01:54:45,048 --> 01:54:45,893
Exactly.

706
01:54:45,974 --> 01:54:48,347
You're in the
lntelligence business!

707
01:54:54,019 --> 01:54:56,794
You've taken care of
the little fish.

708
01:54:56,875 --> 01:55:00,858
I will take care
of the one that got away.

709
01:55:00,938 --> 01:55:02,587
Once Escobedo is gone,

710
01:55:02,627 --> 01:55:05,846
I will be in a position
to help you.

711
01:55:05,926 --> 01:55:09,024
The question is...

712
01:55:09,063 --> 01:55:11,759
what am I supposed
to do with you?

713
01:55:11,839 --> 01:55:12,886
Ugh!

714
01:55:15,058 --> 01:55:16,144
Well?

715
01:55:16,224 --> 01:55:19,603
Guess I'm supposed to
hit you with this bat!

716
01:55:24,310 --> 01:55:26,361
I can also promise you...

717
01:55:26,402 --> 01:55:27,849
Get up!

718
01:55:27,930 --> 01:55:31,269
major arrests that your police
can take credit for...

719
01:55:33,683 --> 01:55:35,895
dramatic seizures,
drastic reductions,

720
01:55:35,975 --> 01:55:37,785
no violence
to speak of.

721
01:55:37,866 --> 01:55:39,716
You'll have your victory.

722
01:55:41,205 --> 01:55:43,458
ln return for what?

723
01:56:21,955 --> 01:56:23,282
Where are they?

724
01:56:23,363 --> 01:56:25,575
They're here.

725
01:56:25,655 --> 01:56:27,023
Seal the plant!

726
01:56:27,104 --> 01:56:28,793
The American killed
Ernesto!

727
01:56:28,874 --> 01:56:31,005
Come on! Move!
Let's go!

728
01:57:16,301 --> 01:57:19,599
Bird to Variable.

729
01:57:33,799 --> 01:57:35,569
Where the hell
are you?

730
01:57:35,650 --> 01:57:36,977
Well, I'm cruisin'

731
01:57:37,057 --> 01:57:40,637
about 5 klicks south
of the village. Over.

732
01:57:40,718 --> 01:57:43,494
Stay there. I'll get
back to you.

733
01:57:43,574 --> 01:57:45,264
Roger that.

734
01:57:56,568 --> 01:57:57,976
No one.

735
01:57:58,015 --> 01:57:59,746
The prisoners.

736
01:58:10,365 --> 01:58:12,980
Oh.

737
01:58:43,673 --> 01:58:46,007
Come on, guys.
Let's go, son.

738
01:58:48,259 --> 01:58:50,753
We're goin' home, boys.

739
02:00:01,632 --> 02:00:04,448
Pick us up at
the Lindo Coffee Factory.

740
02:00:45,600 --> 02:00:46,928
Psst!

741
02:01:30,171 --> 02:01:32,987
From your point of view,

742
02:01:33,067 --> 02:01:36,808
it can eliminate a potential
security problem, does it not?

743
02:01:36,889 --> 02:01:40,228
Not only can I expose you
to the press,

744
02:01:40,349 --> 02:01:42,038
so can the soldiers,

745
02:01:42,119 --> 02:01:44,813
or do you want to take
your chances

746
02:01:46,905 --> 02:01:50,365
ending the political career
of your Commander-ln-Chief?

747
02:02:07,220 --> 02:02:08,467
Aah!

748
02:02:34,856 --> 02:02:36,384
Let's go!

749
02:03:02,652 --> 02:03:07,278
Get your asses in here!
Come on! We got to go!

750
02:03:09,490 --> 02:03:10,898
Come on!

751
02:03:11,060 --> 02:03:13,192
Get your butts in here!

752
02:03:18,099 --> 02:03:20,593
Hold it!
We wait for Ryan!

753
02:03:20,714 --> 02:03:22,806
Yeah? We're out
of here!

754
02:03:29,483 --> 02:03:32,742
Set it down!
He's down there!

755
02:03:44,609 --> 02:03:46,017
Come on!

756
02:04:04,400 --> 02:04:06,371
I got you!

757
02:04:12,445 --> 02:04:15,301
Chavez, cover me!

758
02:04:24,031 --> 02:04:27,370
Your hand!
Give me your hand!

759
02:05:30,042 --> 02:05:32,778
President will
see you now, sir.

760
02:05:44,967 --> 02:05:46,375
Jack.

761
02:05:46,456 --> 02:05:49,271
I'm glad you're here.

762
02:05:49,352 --> 02:05:50,720
Sit down.

763
02:05:50,759 --> 02:05:53,133
Can I get you anything?

764
02:05:53,214 --> 02:05:54,943
No.

765
02:05:56,110 --> 02:05:57,960
Come on. Sit down.

766
02:05:58,041 --> 02:06:00,575
I would prefer
to stand, sir.

767
02:06:02,385 --> 02:06:05,201
Some things have
gone on here

768
02:06:05,241 --> 02:06:07,816
that I'm just
becoming aware of.

769
02:06:07,896 --> 02:06:10,229
I was kept
in the dark--

770
02:06:10,310 --> 02:06:13,125
as you were--
for a very long time.

771
02:06:13,206 --> 02:06:14,211
Troubling things.

772
02:06:14,292 --> 02:06:15,660
Yeah.

773
02:06:15,700 --> 02:06:17,993
Now we have to
figure out

774
02:06:18,073 --> 02:06:19,843
who is responsible
for what

775
02:06:19,924 --> 02:06:22,257
and what to do
about it,

776
02:06:21,333 --> 02:06:25,153
and we have to
do this delicately,

777
02:06:25,194 --> 02:06:28,009
otherwise people might
get the wrong idea.

778
02:06:28,090 --> 02:06:29,658
We have to lie.

779
02:06:30,905 --> 02:06:32,836
Did I say that?

780
02:06:32,917 --> 02:06:35,169
No, you didn't.

781
02:06:35,250 --> 02:06:37,784
You're upset.

782
02:06:37,865 --> 02:06:39,192
I'm upset.

783
02:06:39,273 --> 02:06:41,606
Well,
it's understandable.

784
02:06:41,686 --> 02:06:45,387
You mind if I give you
a bit of advice?

785
02:06:45,428 --> 02:06:48,083
You know this because
you're a smart guy.

786
02:06:48,163 --> 02:06:51,140
Never make important
decisions while you're upset.

787
02:06:51,180 --> 02:06:52,427
You did,

788
02:06:52,508 --> 02:06:54,841
and American soldiers
and innocent civilians

789
02:06:54,921 --> 02:06:56,772
are dead because of it.

790
02:06:56,852 --> 02:06:59,145
I never ordered any--

791
02:06:59,225 --> 02:07:01,799
I will not let you
dishonor their memories

792
02:07:01,840 --> 02:07:04,897
by pretending you had
nothing to do with it.

793
02:07:04,977 --> 02:07:07,391
How dare you
lecture me?

794
02:07:07,472 --> 02:07:09,081
How dare you, sir?

795
02:07:09,161 --> 02:07:11,494
How dare you
bark at me

796
02:07:11,535 --> 02:07:13,345
Iike some little
junkyard dog?

797
02:07:13,385 --> 02:07:16,322
I am the President
of the United States!

798
02:07:19,822 --> 02:07:23,120
It gives me no pleasure
to do it, sir.

799
02:07:23,200 --> 02:07:25,574
As Acting Deputy Director
of lntelligence,

800
02:07:25,654 --> 02:07:28,430
it is my duty to
report this matter

801
02:07:28,511 --> 02:07:30,924
to the Senate
Oversight Committee.

802
02:07:35,228 --> 02:07:37,722
You're not going
to do that.

803
02:07:38,888 --> 02:07:40,296
I'm not?

804
02:07:40,337 --> 02:07:42,348
No, no.

805
02:07:42,429 --> 02:07:47,296
You've got yourself
a chip in the big game now.

806
02:07:47,377 --> 02:07:49,630
You're going to
tuck that away

807
02:07:49,669 --> 02:07:52,404
for a time
when your own ass

808
02:07:52,486 --> 02:07:54,014
is on the line.

809
02:07:54,094 --> 02:07:56,749
Then you're going
to pull it out,

810
02:07:56,790 --> 02:07:59,927
and I'm going to
cash it in for you,

811
02:08:00,007 --> 02:08:01,858
right?

812
02:08:01,899 --> 02:08:05,077
I don't think I
have anything more

813
02:08:05,157 --> 02:08:07,128
to say to you, sir.

814
02:08:07,208 --> 02:08:09,260
The country
can't afford

815
02:08:09,300 --> 02:08:11,874
another scandal,
Jack.

816
02:08:11,955 --> 02:08:13,282
To protect itself,

817
02:08:15,374 --> 02:08:16,702
of another deception

818
02:08:16,783 --> 02:08:19,598
that goes all
the way to the top.

819
02:08:19,679 --> 02:08:21,328
You'll take
the blame.

820
02:08:21,368 --> 02:08:24,224
Cutter and Ritter
will take some, too,

821
02:08:24,264 --> 02:08:27,121
but just a slap
on the wrist

822
02:08:27,160 --> 02:08:29,091
and then $20,000
an hour

823
02:08:29,132 --> 02:08:30,983
on the lecture
circuit.

824
02:08:31,022 --> 02:08:32,873
The rest
of the blame

825
02:08:32,953 --> 02:08:34,924
will fall on Greer.

826
02:08:38,907 --> 02:08:41,763
You'll destroy
his reputation,

827
02:08:41,803 --> 02:08:44,660
but that's as far
as it will go.

828
02:08:44,699 --> 02:08:47,757
The old Potomac
Two-Step, Jack.

829
02:08:50,210 --> 02:08:52,102
I'm sorry,
Mr. President.

830
02:08:52,141 --> 02:08:54,153
I don't dance.

831
02:09:16,077 --> 02:09:18,450
Ryan, have you
got a minute?

832
02:09:18,490 --> 02:09:20,018
No.

833
02:09:21,426 --> 02:09:24,162
We need to talk.

834
02:09:24,243 --> 02:09:26,093
Ryan!

835
02:09:49,384 --> 02:09:52,240
The Committee will please
come to order.

836
02:09:52,280 --> 02:09:55,378
The Chair will now call
Dr. John Ryan.

837
02:10:14,968 --> 02:10:17,342
Dr. Ryan,
thank you very much

838
02:10:17,422 --> 02:10:19,755
for appearing before
the Committee today.

839
02:10:19,795 --> 02:10:21,123
Thank you,
Mr. Chairman.

840
02:10:21,204 --> 02:10:24,382
Please stand
and raise your right hand.

841
02:10:26,715 --> 02:10:28,283
Do you solemnly swear

842
02:10:28,364 --> 02:10:31,179
that the testimony
you're about to give

843
02:10:31,260 --> 02:10:34,075
is the truth, the whole truth,

844
02:10:34,157 --> 02:10:37,616
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

845
02:10:38,943 --> 02:10:40,633
I do.

846
02:10:42,403 --> 02:10:44,615
You may consider yourself
under oath.

847
02:10:44,695 --> 02:10:46,305
Please be seated.


